# next app router

- Prefer Server Components by default. Use Client Components only when browser APIs, interaction, or client-owned state require them.
- Respect App Router file roles. Keep `layout`, `page`, `loading`, `error`, and route handlers aligned with their intended responsibilities.
- Keep client/server boundaries explicit. Do not move data fetching client-side without a clear product or platform reason.
- Keep routing and rendering structure legible. Prefer App Router conventions over custom layout patterns when they solve the problem.
- Model streaming, loading, and error states intentionally when route-level data can be slow or fail.
